parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pedal bounces back and becomes hard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake system becomes unreliable
the rear brakes are not functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A non-functional horn can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver is unable to alert other road users or pedestrians of their presence, particularly in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn does not produce any sound when pressed
the horn produces a weak or faint sound
the horn button is stuck or difficult to press
the horn fails to respond to multiple presses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed shifting can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when accelerating, which can lead to loss of control, accidents, or increased wear on the transmission.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or delays shifting
the vehicle jerks or lurches when accelerating
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle is slow to accelerate.
